title: Eyes Wide Shut - Filming Location
description:
Eyes Wide Shut (1999) is a neo-noir psychological thriller film that is considered a cult film directed, produced and co-written by Stanley Kubrick, based on the 1926 novella Traumnovelle (Dream Story) by Arthur Schnitzler. It was Kubrick's last film before his death. The story, set in and around New York City, follows the surreal, sexually charged adventures of Dr. Bill Harford (Tom Cruise), who is shocked by the revelation by his wife, Alice (Nicole Kidman), that she had contemplated an affair a year earlier. He embarks on a night-long, eventful sexual adventure, during which he infiltrates a massive masked orgy of an underground cult.

This location was used the second time Bill leaves prostitute Domino's (Vinessa Shaw) apartment and is stalked by a man in the street. The man walks along this section of street, whereas Bill walks here: http://wikimapia.org/#lat=51.5200963&lon=-0.108313&z=18&l=0&m=b

title: Roman Wall
description:
Part of the wall built by the Romans.  Also visible underground on the Westbound platform at Tower Hill station, walk almost to the left (east) end of the platform and look for the hole in the opposite wall, with small plaque.

The wall is standing to a surprising height.   The Roman parts have stripes of red brick, the upper parts are medieval.   There is a substantial remnant of one of the medieval gates just to the south.

title: Site of Jack The Ripper Murder 5
description:
Approximate location of Miller's Court, off Dorset Street (Duval Street). There is local trace left - even the street line is no longer visible.

Mary Jane Kelly
Murder #5
Found dead with her body horifically mutilated in her room with her organs laid on the bedside table in a row by the landlord coming up to collect rent. This was the 5th, the worst and generally believed to be the last of Jack The Ripper's murders.
